.DT
describe
$MUDNAME$ player help
describe

.SH Name
.SI 5
describe - set your description
.EI

.SH Syntax
.SI 5
describe clear
describe edit
describe [description]
.EI

.SH Description
.SP 5 5
The describe command is used to put a line about you in your long description
that players get when they look at you.  It is also used in your reference.
When creating a new description remember that your own name will automagically
be inserted as the first word of the description.

Describe with no parameters will print your current description.
Describe clear will clear your description.

Describe edit will drop you into the editor you have chosen and allows you
to edit your description.
.EP

.SH Examples:
.SI 5
> describe is a burly looking man with a tattoo.
Ok.

> describe
Usage: describe <string>
       describe edit
       describe clear
description reads : Shaydz is a burly looking man with a tattoo.

> describe clear
Description cleared.
.EI

.SH See also
.SI 5
chfn, look, editor, refer
.EI
